.TH man atlas-simple_shell 1 "2024-07-21" "1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
atlas-simple_shell \- a custom Unix shell implementaion

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B atlas-simple_shell
.RI [options]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B atlas-simple_shell
is a custom Unix shell that replicates the functionality of a traditional
Unix shell. It reads commands from standard input, executes them, and
handles errors. The shell provides a prompt for the user input and 
supports the execution of commands with and without arguments. It also
implements built-in commands like 'exit' and 'env', and uses the PATH
environment variable to locate executables.

.SH EXAMPLES
Here are some examples of how to use
.B atlas-simple_shelll
.PP
To start the shell:
.RS
.nf
\fC$ ./hsh\fR
.fi
.RE

.PP
To execute a command:
.RS
.nf
\fC($) /bin/ls\fR
.fi
.RE

.PP
To use the 'exit' built-in command:
.RS
.nf
\fC($) exit\fR
.fi
.RE

.PP
To use the 'env' built-in command:
.RS
.nf
\fC($) env\fR
.fi
.RE

